It did not take long for the host nation to win its first gold at the Beijing Winter Olympics, with success coming on day one and fittingly in China's best discipline, short track speed skating. The quick quartet of Fan Kexin, Qu Chunyu, Ren Ziwei and Wu Dajing stormed to a thrilling victory in the first-ever Olympic mixed relay final at the Capital Indoor Stadium in Beijing. Sports Scene's anchor Wang Dong reviewed the victory.